de nas byang chub sems dpa' 'jam dpal gyis byang chub sems dpa' rin chen dpal la 'di skad ces smras so/ /

kye rgyal ba'i sras dag/ sems can thams cad kyi 'byung ba chen po bzhi rnams yongs su 'dzin pa med cing bdag gi med la mnyam pa yin yang 'on kyang bde ba'i tshor ba dag kyang snang / sdug bsngal gyi tshor ba dag kyang snang / yid du 'ong bar byed pa dang / yid du mi 'ong bar byed pa dang / nang du byed pa dang / phyi rol tu byed pa dang / tshor ba chung ba dang / tshor ba che ba dang / tshe 'di la myong ba dang / tshe gzhan la myong ba dag kyang snang la/ chos kyi dbyings la ni/ yid du 'ong ba'am/ yid du mi 'ong ba yang med pa 'di ci zhig ;

de nas byang chub sems dpa' rin chen dpal gyis byang chub sems dpa' 'jam dpal la tshigs su bcad de smras pa/

de nas byang chub sems dpa' 'jam dpal gyis byang chub sems dpa' ye shes dpal la 'di skad ces smras so; ;

kye rgyal ba'i sras/ de ste de bzhin gshegs pa'i bstan pa ni/ ye shes sngon du 'gro ba yin na/ de ci'i phyir de bzhin gshegs pa sems can la la la ni/ sbyin pa brjod pa mdzad/ la la la ni/ tshul khrims/ la la la ni/ bzod pa/ la la la ni/ brtson 'grus/ la la la ni/ bsam gtan/ la la la ni/ shes rab brjod pa mdzad/ la la la ni/ byams pa/ la la la ni/ snying rje/ la la la ni/ dga' ba/ la la la ni/ btang snyoms brjod pa mdzad kyang bla na med pa yang dag par rdzogs pa'i byang chub tu ni/ chos gcig 'gas 'byung bar mi nus so/ /
de nas byang chub sems dpa' ye shes dpal gyis byang chub sems dpa' 'jam dpal la tshigs su bcad de smras pa/

byang chub sems dpa' 'jam dpal gyis byang chub sems dpa' ye shes dpal la 'di skad ces smras so/ /
kye rgyal ba'i sras/ khyod de ltar skye bo mang po la phan pa dang / skye bo mang po la bde ba dang / 'jig rten la snying brtse ba dang / lha dang mi rnams kyi don dang / phan pa dang / bde ba dang / bde bar rnam par gzud pa'i phyir zhugs shing / de ltar khyod rnam pa 'di lta bu'i gnas dag yongs su dri bar sems pa ni/ kye rgyal ba'i sras/ legs so/ / legs so/ /
kye rgyal ba'i sras/ byang chub sems dpa' dag gi sems kyi las yid la byed pa'i sbyor ba gang dang ldan pas/ byang chub sems dpa' rnams yon tan gyi khyad par 'di dag thams cad 'thob par 'gyur pa dang / sangs rgyas kyi chos thams cad la thogs pa med pa'i lus su 'gyur ba dang / sangs rgyas bcom ldan 'das 'das pa dang / ma byon pa dang / da ltar byung ba rnams kyi lam du 'jug pa dang / sems can thams cad yongs su mi gtong ba'i sems kyang de dag la nye bar gnas pa dang / chos thams cad ji lta ba bzhin du rnam par lta ba yang de dag la nye bar gnas pa dang / mi dge ba'i chos thams cad spangs par 'gyur ba dang / dge ba'i chos thams cad dang ldan par 'gyur ba dang / kun tu bzang zhing kun tu mdzes pa dang / rnam pa'i mchog thams cad dang ldan pa dang / chos thams cad la dbang sgyur zhing srog chags thams cad la ston pa gnyis par 'gyur ba'i sems kyi las yid la byed pa'i sbyor ba yod de/ kye rgyal ba'i sras dag /byang chub sems dpa' sems kyi las yid la byed pa'i sbyor ba gang dang ldan pas/ yon tan gyi khyad par 'di dag thams cad 'thob par 'gyur ba'i byang chub sems dpa'i sems kyi las yid la byed pa'i sbyor ba de dag gang zhe na/ kye rgyal ba'i sras;

de yang 'dod pa'i sred pa rgyal srid dang / / bdag bde'i don dang grags dang snyan phyir min/ / 'gro ba'i sdug bsngal ma lus gzhil ba'i phyir/ / 'jig rten phan skyed sems ni yongs su skye; ;
de ni sems can rtag tu bde don dang / / zhing sbyangs sangs rgyas mang po mchod pa'i rgyur/ / yongs su chos 'dzin byang chub 'tshang rgya zhing / / ye shes rnam par sbyong ba'i sems skye 'o; ;
rgyal ba kun dang chos dang dge 'dun dang / / de bzhin bla mar gyur pa thams cad la/ / dad dang mos pa dga' ba bskyed byas te/ / sri zhur mchod byas byang chub sems kyang skye; ;
rgyal ba bde gshegs chos la yid ches nas/ / rgyal sras spyod pa rnams la yid ches te/ / byang chub bla na med la yid ches shing / / skyes bu dam pa rnams kyi sems skye 'o/ /
dad pa sngon 'gro ma ltar bskyed pa ste/ / yon tan thams cad yongs su skyong zhing 'dren/ / nem nur rnam sel nad las rab tu sgrol/ / dad pa bde ba'i grong du phyin par byed/ /

de dag sangs rgyas stobs bcu mi 'jigs bzhi/ / chos kyi khyad par bco brgyad rnams kyis kyang / / sangs rgyas bdag nyid che brjod byed cing / / sangs rgyas yon tan rnams kyis 'gro don byed/ /
de dag yongs ston rdzu 'phrul rjes ston gyi/ / gzugs rnams byin rlob mthu yis mthu che ba/ / de bzhin gshegs pa'i rdzu 'phrul ston byed cing / / rdzu 'phrul rnam par 'phrul bas sems can 'dul/ /
de dag thabs kyi tshul mang sna tshogs kyi/ / 'gro ba'i don du 'jig rten rim gror byed/ / 'jig rten mi chags chu la pad+mo bzhin/ / dga' ba mos pa skye bar rnam par spyod/ /
de dag rjod byed brjod pa'i rgyal ba byed/ / gar mkhan rnga mkhan gyad dang rol mo mkhan/ / mdzes shing sdug par bzhad gad byed pa dang / / sgyu mkhan gzugs med kun tu ston par byed/ /
grong ba grong dpon kha lo sgyur ba dang / / ded dpon tshong dpon khyim bdag de bzhin te/ / rgyal po blon po mnga' rab pho nya dang / / sman pa mi 'jigs gtsug lag mkhas pa byed; ;
de dag nags tshal sdong po chen por 'gyur/ / sman dang rin chen mi zad gter dag dang / / yid bzhin nor bu 'dod pa 'byin shing dang / / lam gol 'khyams la de bzhin lam ston 'gyur; ;
'jig rten byung nas mi ring shes gyur cing / / sems can las kyi tshul la mi shes pa/ / de dag kun la rmos thabs tshong thabs dang / / sna tshogs bzo rnams kun kyang rjod par byed/ /
'tshe med gnod pa med pa'i sbyor ba rnams/ / sems can bde skyed mkhas pas rab bsngags pa/ / rig mthu sman dang gtsug lag sna tshogs rnams/ / kun kyang drang srong de dag rnam par brjod; ;
drang srong rnams kyi spyod pa dam pa'i mchog / gang la lhar bcas 'jig rten dad gyur dang / / brtul zhugs dka' spyod dka' thub mchog gi rnams/ / kun kyang mkhas pa de dag ston par byed/ /
de dag rgyu dang kun rgyu mu stegs can/ / dka' thub spyod yul mi smrar spyod pa dang / / sgren mo gos med ri yi dge sbyong la/ / mu stegs can gyi mkhan po mkhas pa byed/ /

'od zer mi 'jigs sbyin pa rab bkye zhing / / 'jigs mnar sems can ji snyed des phog pa/ /
'byung po bza' dang bsad cing brdog pa dang / / nad kyi 'jigs pa kun las rab tu 'grol/ / mi 'jigs sbyin pas sems can bskyabs pa dang / / srog gcod las las sems rgyud phyir bzlog cing / /
'jigs pas skyabs tshol rnams la bskyabs byas pas/ / 'od zer mi 'jigs sbyin pa des grub bo; ;

Entering right concentration in the eye-organ, Emerging from concentration in the field of form, Showing the inconceivability of the nature of form, Unknowable to all gods and men; Entering right concentration in the field of form And emerging from concentration in the eye, without disturbing the mind, Explaining the eye is birthless and has no origin, By nature empty, null, and doing nothing;
Entering right concentration in the ear faculty And emerging from concentration in the field of sound, Distinguishing the sounds of all languages, Unknowable to gods and men, Entering right concentration in the field of sound, Emerging from concentration in the ear, the mind undisturbed, Explaining the ear is birthless and has no origin, By nature empty, null, and doing nothing;
Entering right concentration in the nose faculty And emerging from concentration in the field of scent, Discovering all the most excellent fragrances, Unknowable to gods and men, Entering right concentration in the field of scent, Emerging from concentration in the nose, mind undisturbed, Explaining the nose is birthless and has no origin, Empty by nature, null, and doing nothing;
Entering right concentration in the tongue faculty, Emerging from concentration in the field of flavor, Discovering all the most exquisite flavors Unknowable to gods and men, Entering right concentration in the field of flavor, Emerging from concentration in the tongue, mind undisturbed, Explaining the tongue is birthless and has no origin, By nature, empty, null, and doing nothing;
Entering right concentration in the faculty of the body, Emerging from concentration in the field of touch, Able to clearly distinguish all textures, Unknowable to gods and men, Entering right concentration in the field of touch, Emerging from concentration in the body, mind undisturbed, Explaining the body is birthless and has no origin, By nature empty, null, and doing nothing;
Entering right concentration in the mental faculty, Emerging from concentration in the field of phenomena, Discerning the characteristics of all things, Unknowable to gods and men, Entering right concentration in the field of phenomena, Emerging from concentration in the mental organ, mind undisturbed, Explaining the mind is birthless and has no origin, By nature empty, null, and doing nothing;

The various voices of men and women,
The calls of birds and beasts,
The sounds of oceans, rivers, and thunder,
Can all delight sentient beings’ minds—
How much the more one who knows the nature of sound is like echoes,
Who attains to unhindered, wonderful eloquence,
And teaches the truth as appropriate to each,
Is able to bring joy to the creatures of the world.

The ocean has a special extraordinary quality—
It can be an equal reflector of all;
Sentient beings, precious things, rivers and streams—
All it contains, prohibiting none.
One with inexhaustible meditation, concentration, and liberation,
Can also be a seal of equanimity, equally reflecting, like this;
The wonderful practices of virtue and knowledge
This one cultivates all without tiring.
When the dragon kings of the ocean roam about,
They are free wherever they may be,
Producing clouds covering the earth,
Those clouds of various decorative colors:
In the sixth heaven, of access to others’ enjoyments,
The clouds are the color of gold;
In the heaven of enjoyment of emanations they’re the color of ruddy pearls;
In the heaven of happiness, they’re the color of frost and snow;
In the heaven of timely portion they’re the color of lapis lazuli;
In the heaven of thirty-three celestial realms they’re opal colored;
In the heaven of the four kings they’re crystal colored;
Over the oceans, they’re diamond colored;
Among kinnaras they’re incense colored;
In the dragons’ abodes they’re lotus colored;
Where yakshas live, the color of white geese;
Among titans, the color of mountain rocks;
In the region of Uttara, the color of golden flames;
In Jambudvipa, the color of sapphire;
In the other continents, their adornments are mixed—
These are given according to the likes of the creatures.

Also in the heaven of access to others’ enjoyments
Lightning in the clouds shines like sunlight;
In the heaven of enjoyment of emanations, it’s like moonlight;
In the heaven of happiness, like rose gold;
In the timely portion heaven, it’s the color of jadelike snow;
In the thirty-threefold heaven, the color of golden flames;
In the four kings’ heaven, the color of all jewels;
In the ocean, the color of red pearls;
In the realm of the kinnaras, the color of lapis lazuli;
In the abode of dragons, the colors of a mine of jewels;
Where the yakshas live, the color of crystal;
Among the titans, the color of onyx;
In the realm of Uttara, the color of fiery pearls;
In Jambudvipa, the color of sapphires;
In the other continents, the embellishments are mixed—
As are the colors of the clouds, so is the lightning.

In the heaven of access to others’ enjoyments, thunder is like the voice of Brahma;
In the heaven of enjoyment of emanations, it’s like the sound of great drums;
In the heaven of happiness it’s like the sound of singing;
In the heaven of timely portion it’s like the voices of goddesses;
In the heaven of thirty-three celestial regions
It’s like the various sounds of kinnaras;
In the heaven of the four world-guarding kings
It’s like the sounds produced by grandharvas;
In the ocean it sounds like mountains crashing together;
Among the kinnaras, it’s the sound of pipes,
In the castles of the dragons, it sounds like the call of kalavinka birds;
In the yakshas’ abode it’s like the voices of dragon maidens;
Among the titans, it sounds like a celestial drum;
Among humans, it’s like the sound of the surf.
